{The Big Baler.} { This machine is also pulled by a tractor. It collects the straw or hay lying on the ground and binds it into large, round bales. These are stored in long stacks. The big bales are easier to roll out as bedding or winter feed for the animals.
{The Low Ground Pressure Vehicle.}
This vehicle is made of lightweight alluminium. It has eight wheels to spread the weight. It is about 2.5m long and very low. The cab is very small and has a calculator in it to work out how much of the field has been treated. It is used when the ground is too wet for a tractor to spray crops.
